@startuml
' @id(SEQ-TEST-VALIDATE)
' @ref(USE-TEST-COVERAGE)
' @desc(SEQ-TEST-VALIDATE, "Objective flow for the test rules inside Project::validate_inner. The engine builds one unified test view by reading Trace.tests and projecting the legacy generated_tests/generated_ui_tests (DOM-TEST-PROJECTION). For each link it checks the file exists and model_id is known (ERROR), and — only when config.test.layers is non-empty — that layer/framework are members of the profile (USE-TEST-LAYER-MEMBERSHIP). Then, ONLY when layers are configured, for every implementation-bearing @id it checks at least one linked test of the expected layer (USE-TEST-COVERAGE); a gap BLOCKS when test.gate=error and WARNS when gate=warn. With no configured layers the coverage and membership rules are inert (safe-by-default). No test is executed — this is the structural gate only.")
' Current sequence for Cycle A: validate over the unified test view.
' Structural existence/linkage/membership/coverage only; no execution.
title mdd validate — test rules (current)

participant "Project::validate_inner" as V
participant "trace.yml\ntests + generated_*" as Trace
participant "projection\n(DOM-TEST-PROJECTION)" as Proj
participant "config.yml\ntest.gate + test.layers" as Cfg
participant "ValidationReport\n{errors, warnings}" as Rep

V -> Trace : read tests + generated_*
V -> Proj : project legacy into unified TestLink view
Proj --> V : Vec<TestLink>
V -> Cfg : read test.gate + test.layers

loop each TestLink
  V -> V : path exists? model_id known?
  alt missing file or unknown id
    V -> Rep : ERROR
  end
  alt layers configured
    V -> V : layer/framework in test.layers?
    alt not a member
      V -> Rep : ERROR (no longer a silent drop)
    end
  end
end

alt layers configured
  loop each implementation-bearing @id
    V -> V : >=1 linked test of expected layer?
    alt none
      alt gate=error
        V -> Rep : ERROR
      else
        V -> Rep : WARNING
      end
    end
  end
else no layers (Cycle A default)
  V -> V : coverage inert (safe-by-default)
end

Rep --> V : ok = no blocking errors
@enduml
